getPreProcessing

Operation getPreProcessing()
Gets the preProcessing operation. Operation that runs before the main processing. This operation can contain any initialization required before the main processing. If this parameter is null, then the batch process will omit the pre-processing step.

Returns:

getInputPropertyName

String getInputPropertyName()
Gets the inputPropertyName. Name of the property of the operationClass that takes the input. Elements fetched by the query are set to this property before being processed by the operation. The type of this property must be such that it accepts the elements fetched by the query.

Returns:
Returns the inputPropertyName

Parameters:

getFormatter

Formatter<T> getFormatter()
Gets the formatter. Class of the formatter. Each queue processor of this batch process has its own formatter that is instantiated by the default factory. The formatters are used to print the processed elements in the log files. The formatter can be null. In this case a default formatter will be used that prints the result of the element's toString() method.

Returns:
Returns the formatter

setFormatter

void setFormatter(Formatter<T> formatter)
Assigns a new value to the formatter. Must be a thread safe formatter, because it is being used by all queueProcessors.

Parameters:
formatter - the formatter to set

getMonitoringMailRecipients

String getMonitoringMailRecipients()
Gets a string that contains a comma separated list of recipiens for a status mail.
If this parameter is not empty, then a monitoring mail will be sent periodically. The interval between two subsequent messages is defined by setMonitoringMailInterval(int).

Returns:
Returns a string with the recipient mail addresses of the monitoring mail.

setMonitoringMailRecipients

void setMonitoringMailRecipients(String monitoringMailRecipients)
Sets the recipients for a monitoring mail.

Parameters:
monitoringMailRecipients - List with the mail recipients. If this is null or empty ,then no message will be sent.

getMonitoringMailInterval

int getMonitoringMailInterval()
Gets the time interval in minutes between two subsequent monitoring messages. If this parameter is set to null or empty, then no message will be sent.

Returns:
Returns the monitoring mail interval.

setMonitoringMailInterval

void setMonitoringMailInterval(int monitoringMailInterval)

monitoringMailInterval - Interval in minutes

getNamedInputFiles

Map<String,String> getNamedInputFiles()
Gets the input files for this batch process. The key is the logical name of the stream and the value the actual filesystem path.
This may be null indicating that there are no input files to setup. TODO: This property exists for the support of submitted jobs running in parallel. It will be refactored.

Returns:
Returns input files for this batch process.
